\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 is nonconvex 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
NC-ADMM and NC-DRS are not equivalent 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
reasons for the loss of equivalency:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
strict duality gap
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\Pi}_{\mathop{{\bf conv}}\mathcal{C}}\neq\mathbf{\tilde{\Pi}}_{\mathcal{C}}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Moreau's decomposition does not hold
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
NC-ADMM in 
\family typewriter
\color blue
NCVX-CVXPY
\family default
\color inherit
 works on a modified dual, hence produces a lower objective value
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
relationship between minimizers of the original problem and the NC-ADMM
 operator breaks down
\end_layout

\end_deeper
