\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
total deviation of 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{R}$
\end_inset

 from being a nonexpansive operator over the sequence 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \left(z_{n},z\right)\right\} _{n\in\mathbf{N}}$
\end_inset

 is bounded
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
depends on the initial point
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
in our case 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 is not necessarily convex
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
but, if we take 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 to be convex then 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
total deviation of 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{R}$
\end_inset

 from being a nonexpansive operator over the sequence 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \left(z_{n},z\right)\right\} _{n\in\mathbf{N}}$
\end_inset

 is zero
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
our convergence proof coincides with known convergence results for convex
 setup
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

